  "storyline": "# Storyline\n\n## Context\n\nDPSY & Associates required financial reporting workflows that could turn fragmented account, CRM, inventory, and client data into cleaner review outputs.\n\n## Workflow\n\nThe work moved from source review and data consolidation into segmentation, dashboarding, forecasting, and recurring report preparation. CRM reconciliation separated routine records from higher-risk cases, while BI dashboards made client-facing reporting easier to scan.\n\n## Technical Implementation\n\n- **CRM reconciliation:** filtered routine account records and surfaced higher-risk cases through segmentation logic.\n- **Dashboarding:** built Tableau and Power BI reporting surfaces for recurring client metrics.\n- **Data consolidation:** created 5+ ETL-style workflows to normalize source data and reduce drift across reports.\n- **Inventory analysis:** combined market research and stocking-level analysis to support operational recommendations.\n- **Financial modeling:** used SQL, Python, Excel, and forecasting workflows for recurring financial analysis.\n\n## Outcomes\n\nThe work improved reporting consistency, supported 10+ dashboard outputs, reduced routine review load through CRM filtering, and created cleaner data surfaces for client and audit support."
